# Next.js frontend patterns

## App Router only
Use App Router exclusively. No pages/ directory patterns.
Default to React Server Components.
Add "use client" only when interactivity is required.

## Styling
Tailwind CSS only. No inline styles. No CSS modules. No styled-components.

## Images — performance critical
```tsx
// Always use next/image
import Image from 'next/image';

// Always specify width and height (prevents CLS)
<Image src={url} alt="description" width={640} height={480} />

// For user-uploaded images use picture with AVIF first
<picture>
  <source type="image/avif" srcSet="image.avif" />
  <source type="image/webp" srcSet="image.webp" />
  <img src="image.jpg" alt="..." width={640} height={480} loading="lazy" />
</picture>
```

## Performance budgets
- Landing page: max 500KB total (HTML + CSS + JS + critical images)
- Dashboard: max 800KB total
- Never import a heavy library without checking bundle impact first
- Use next/dynamic with ssr:false for heavy client-only components

## Data fetching
Prefer server-side data fetching in Server Components.
Use React Query or SWR only for real-time client-side data.
